lines.text: you took the tun-nel route home
you've nev-er tak-en that way with me be-fore
did you feel the need for change?
a-pol-o-gies on your fin-ger-nails
love flick-ered in the cit-y of lights,
like in-ter-mit-tent ra-di-o waves
i don't need your tears
i don't want your love
i just got-ta get home
and i feel like i'm break-ing up, and i want-ed to stay
head-lights on the hill-side, don't take me this way
i don't want you to hold me, i don't want you to pray
this is big-ger than us

guilt smeared a-cross your lips
i was tired and cold from the window
